# Tech Stack & Architecture Rules

## Frontend

- Framework: React.js (Vite build tool)
- UI Library: Material UI (MUI)
- Pattern: Build modular, accessible components.

## Backend

- Framework: Node.js with Express
- API Style: RESTful endpoints serving JSON.

## Database

- Engine: PostgreSQL
- Persistence: Always use named Docker volumes for database data.

## Infrastructure & Docker (Mac M2 Max & Windows WSL 2 Compatibility)

- Architecture: Always prefer native `arm64` container images for Apple Silicon compatibility. Do not force `amd64` emulation unless strictly necessary.
- Volumes: Use relative bind mounts for local development to enable hot-reloading (e.g., `./frontend:/app`).
- File Sharing: Design for VirtioFS on Mac and the Linux filesystem on Windows WSL 2.
